To terminate a C program, you can use the `return` statement. In the `main` function, simply include `return 0;` at the end. This will effectively terminate the program. Here's an example:

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    // Your program logic goes here

    // Terminate the program
    return 0;
}
```

By including `return 0;` at the end of the `main` function, you are indicating that the program has executed successfully and has reached its end. This will cause the program to terminate.

